23/01/2004
BANJA LUKA, Republika Srpska -- Parliament on Thursday (22 January) approved an initiative to amend the entity's constitution. Lawmakers decided that parliament should review a draft amendment to the main law, envisioning Banja Luka as the RS entity capital, rather than Sarajevo, which is stipulated as the main city in Article 9 of the constitution. Parliament also decided to accept for consideration draft provisions envisioning the transfer of competencies from RS to the BiH state. A parliamentary commission was asked to work on the draft amendments and submit them to parliament in the coming days. (RTRS, PBS BiH - 22/01/04)
